docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:86:- 002I completed the object-level permission test harness. `sfpcl_credit.identity.modules.object_permissions.evaluate_object_access(...)` is a pure domain-neutral helper that accepts only explicit actor facts (`actor_user_id`, `actor_team_codes`, `actor_permission_codes`) and object facts (`required_permission`, `object_owner_user_id`, `object_team_code`, optional `allow_global`). It returns `ObjectAccessResult(allowed, reason, error_code, required_permission, approval_required)`; missing module permission returns `missing_permission` / `PERMISSION_DENIED`; owner and team matches allow; mismatched or unknown scope returns `owner_mismatch`, `team_mismatch`, or `scope_unknown` with `OBJECT_ACCESS_DENIED`; `scope_unknown` sets `approval_required=True`; explicit `allow_global=True` permits unknown scope only after the required canonical permission is present. Tests verify use with `auth_service.effective_permission_codes(user)`, `User.team_codes()`, and `auth_service.team_payload(user)`. No endpoint, schema change, domain model query, audit row, or frontend change.
